{"/service/ndnp/az/batch_az_iotite_ver01/data/sn84020064/0054286641A/1930051001/0006.xml":{"full_text":"SIX\nSweeping Change\nIn Trial Rules\nAgreed at Meet\nRevision of Criminal Code\nand Common Law Re\nstatement Considered.\nWASHINGTON. May 9 (<V-Vir\ntual agreement upon further recom\nmendations for a wholesale revi\nsion of the nation's criminal code,\nand the completion of another step\nin an 18-year task of \u201crestating'' the\ncountry's common law, stood accom\nplished tonight by 600 leading\njurists and barristers at the eighth\nannual meeting of the American\nLaw Institute.\nDuring the day. for the sake of\nspeedier deliberation, the institute\ndivided into two One con-\nsidered the final chapters of a\nvoluminous \u201cmodel code of criminal 1\nprocedure.\u201d The other debated 1\npoints of the common law.\n\nNominee Is Member.\nAt one point, however, the two\nmet on common ground\u2014congrat-\nulating Owen J. Roberts upon his\nnomination by President Hoover to\nday to the supreme court. Roberts\nis a member of the institute\u2019s coun\ncil, and if his nomination is con\nfirmed will be the third member of\nthat body to be elevated to the\nhighest tribunal within the past\nfive years. He attended the open\ning sessions yesterday.\nOne change was made today in\nthe \u201cmodel code\u2019\u2019 by the justices,\njudges and lawyers umaidering iu\nThe point involved a provision for\nfacilitating the summoning of wit\nnesses from other states, and the\nentire section was withdrawn when\nit was found in partial conflict\nwith a plan to accomplish the same\nend. formulated by another law\nbody. A committee was appointed\nto harmonize the differences.\n\nCharge Jury Selection.\nA vote on the remaining sections\nin the 12 chapters of the proposed\ncode not yet approved was scheu\nuled for tomorrow. After debate\nlasting until midnight last night\nmore than half of the proposals\nwere approved.\nMajor proposals already ap\nproved would call for the selection\nof extra jurors in protracted trials;\nthe examination of jurors by the\njudge rather than by the opposing\ncounsel; permission to defendants\nto waive jury trial in other than\ncapital cases; the issuance of a\nsummons rather than a warrant ol\narrest in minor cases; and a simpli\nfication of the form* of indictments.\nMaricopa Census\nTo Total 150,000,\nIs Claim Advanced\nPHOENIX. May 9 W) Orme\nLewis, census supervisor for Mari\ncopa and Yuma counties, announc\ned tonight that Maricopa county,\nexcluding Indians living on reser\nvations, and five small voting pre\ncincts where the census count still\nis incomplete, has a population of\n147,918. He said the Indian popu\nlation and that in the five pre\ncincts is expected to bring the coun\nty total to more than 150.000.\nThe Maricopa county count in\n1920 was 98.576.\nYuma county\u2019s 1930 count, Lewis\nsaid, shows 16,494, exclusive of In\n_ dians\u2014not yet counted\u2014as compar\ned with 14.904 in 1920, an increase\nof 10 per cent.\nATLANTA PLANS POLICE RADIO\nATLANTA. \u2014Atlanta is plan\nning the adoption of the radio as\na means of running down crimi\nnals. The plans calls for a central\nstation from which information\nconcerning crimes would be broad\ncast to police cars equipped with\nreceiving sets In all parts of the\ncity.\nDispatch Telephones\u2014Bl-82.\nNacozari Railroad Co.\nB. O. LONG\nTRAFFIC MANAGER\nTues. Mon\nThurs. Wed\nNo.l TIME CARD No. 20 No. t\n6:15 Lv Agua Prieta ...Ar. 21:30\n1:45 Cabullona 10:50\n9:12 Cima 10:30\n9:50 Fronteras 9:55\n10:10 Cuchuta 9:20\n10:33 Esqueda 9:12\n10:44 Turicachi 8:52\n10JO Vigia 8:38\n11:30 Calabasas 8:18\nU:3d El Tajo 8.03\n11:39 San Nicolas 7:51\n11:55 Purica -1\u2014 7:34\n12:05 Hidalgo 7:30\n12:30 Ar Nacozari Lv. 7:00\nSame\nPrice\nfor over 38 years\n2^ ounces for 25^\nUSE LESS\nthan of high\npriced brands\nMILLIONS OF FOUNDS\nUSED BY OUI COVBBNMENI\nGadsden Arrivals\nE. V. Malley. Phoenix; Frank\nCuman, Los Angeles; Henry W\nSwofford. Los Angeles; L. R